# Golang Coding Style
- Always format code using `gofmt` or `go fmt`.
- Never manually adjust indentation or spacing.
- Use tabs for indentation (Go default).
- Keep line length around 100 characters.

# C++ Coding Style
- Code must be readable, maintainable, and consistent.
- Prefer modern C++ (C++17 or later).
- Avoid overly complex abstractions.